                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/864.</note>
                <head>[Memorandum—Translation.]</head>
                <p>With all due reserves, this embassy informs the Department of State that the
                    Government of Mexico has heard of the miscarriage of certain papers taken from
                    the rebel Martín Casillas at El Paso, Tex., and forwarded to the district
                    attorney of that city.</p>
                <p>The said papers are letters from Abraham Gonzales to Soto and Orozco, dated
                    February 11, and communications of Francisco I. Madero to his brother Raul, all
                    bearing on the movement headed by Madero and being organized on American
                    territory.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Embassy of Mexico</hi>,<lb/>
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-03-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 1, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
